\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. O. spruneri} Nyman, {\i Consp.} 698 (1882). Plant 10-30 cm. Basal leaves 3-6, oblong-lanceolate, acute. Spike 2- to 4-flowered, lax. Perianth-segments green or greenish-purple, rarely white, pink or purple; outer 8-10 mm, oblong-ovate to -lanceolate; inner 5-8 mm, at least ½ as long as the outer, lanceolate or oblong, subobtuse to acute, glabrous or hairy. Labellum 10-13(-15) × 10-13(-15) mm, orbicular, ovate or obovate, blackish-brown or -purple, 3-lobed, very rarely subentire; lateral lobes ovate, convex, deflexed, rarely almost patent; middle lobe much longer than the lateral, semi-orbicular, reniform or oblong, the margin usually strongly deflexed; speculum bluish-violet, with white margin. Connective acute. •{\i  Greece and Aegean region; Sicilia.} Cr Gr Si.
