\pard\f0\fs28   Plants of hybrid origin between{\b  9} and{\b  6}({\b d}) have been called {\i O. bertoloniiformis} O. & E. Danesch, {\i Orchidee}{\b  22}: 117 (1971); they differ from {\b 9} chiefly in being 15-25 cm high, in having both the inner and outer perianth-segments greenish and more or less undulate, and the labellum 10-12 × 9-11 mm, scarcely curved upwards and without or with an inconspicuous appendage. They have 2n = 36. Because of frequent confusion between this and {\b 9} the distribution given above refers to both these taxa.{\i  O. bertholoniiformis} is probably the more widespread, and {\b 9} is perhaps confined to the E. part of the range. {\b O. promontorii} O. & E. Danesch, {\i op. cit.} 258 (1971), described from S.E. Italy (Mte Gargano), is probably of hybrid origin between{\b  9} and {\i O. garganica} (vide {\b 6}). It has 2n = 36, 37, 38.
